header.gameNote: ATLANTIC SUN MEN'S CHAMPIONSHIP - QUARTERFINALS AT MACON GA

article.headline: Jacksonville 76, North Florida 69
article.story: MACON, Ga. -- Ben Smith and Lehmon Colbert scored 24 points each to lead Jacksonville to a 76-69 victory over North Florida on Wednesday night in the first round of the Atlantic Sun Conference tournament. The Dolphins (19-11) play the winner of Thursday night's game between Mercer and Belmont in the semifinals at 9 p.m. Friday. Jacksonville, which shared the regular-season title with Lipscomb, Belmont and Campbell, had to hold off a rally by North Florida over the final 2 minutes. The Ospreys (13-18) pulled to within 73-69 with 20 seconds left. Colbert scored 12 points in the first half, which ended with the Dolphins leading 34-28. Eni Cuka had 10 of his team-high 24 points for North Florida in the opening half. Jacksonville won all three games against its city rival this season, taking 62-55 and 73-61 victories in the regular season.
